headline.main: Allies Hit Rabaul, Bag 45 Planes; AMERICANS BATTLE ON CHOISEUL ISLE

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN THE SOUTHEST PACIFIC, Monday, Nov. 1 (AP) -- The important Japanese air base at Rabaul, on New Britain Island, suffered another of Gen. Douglas MacArthur's sledgehammer blows on Friday. A strong force of Liberators, escorted by Lightnings, destroyed forty-
abstract: US planes raid Vunakanau airdrome, Rabaul; down 25 intercepting planes; destroy 20-25 others by bombing; Australian planes raid Tobera airdrome, Rabaul; Allied light naval craft sink large Jap barge and escort ship off Blucher Pt, New Guinea
